# Excludes generated, infrastructure, and documentation files from scanning.
# Each exclusion is documented with its justification.

# MkDocs generated output (HTML, JS, search index) — not source code
site/

# Backup files should not be in the repo; exclude from scan rather than fix
agents/orchestrator.py.bak

# Example / reference files: contain illustrative connection strings,
# not production code that executes with those values.
.env.example

# Documentation files: Semgrep flags YAML/markdown connection-string examples
# (postgres sslmode, redis URLs) in documentation. These are illustrative only.
SKILL.md
TROUBLESHOOTING.md
docs/

# Operations scripts: container-privileged and other infra patterns are expected
start_all.sh

# Test files: Redis URLs in tests are mock/test infrastructure, not production connections
tests/

# Docker Compose infrastructure configuration:
#   - wget healthchecks hit localhost:<port> (internal container-to-container;
#     not an external unencrypted transport concern)
#   - Port bindings to 0.0.0.0 are expected for Docker service discovery
#   - Redis/Postgres connections are internal data_net with password auth
# Findings: wget-unencrypted-url, port-all-interfaces, redis-unencrypted-transport,
#            postgres-insecure-sslmode
docker-compose.yml
